{{Infobox church | name = Båstad Church | fullname = | other name = St. Mary's Church | native_name = Båstads kyrka | native_name_lang = swe | image = Mariakyrkan i Båstad, maj 2015.jpg | caption = Båstad Church in May 2015 | location = [[Båstad]], [[Skåne County|Skåne]] | country = [[Sweden]] | denomination = [[Church of Sweden]] | diocese = [[Diocese of Lund]] }}
'''Båstad Church''' ({{lang-sv|Båstads kyrka}}), also known as '''St. Mary's Church''' (''Mariakyrkan''), is a medieval [[Lutheran]] church built in the [[Romanesque architecture|Romanesque]] style. Located in [[Båstad]], seat of [[Skåne County]] in southern [[Sweden]], it belongs to the [[Diocese of Lund]].<ref>[http://www.bjareslaktring.org/node/60 "Båstad"], Bjäre Släktring. {{sv icon}} Retrieved 9 September 2013.</ref>
==History and architecture== The church was built in the [[Romanesque architecture|Romanesque]] style in the 15th century. Remarkably large for its day, it consisted of a [[nave]] flanked on either side by [[aisle]]s. The hexagonal choir wall at the eastern end of the building was completed in the 1470s and is reminiscent of that in [[St. Mary's Church, Ystad|St Mary's Church]], [[Ystad]]. The brick tower was built around 1500, giving the church is present appearance.
==Interior== The font, inscribed with runes, perpetuates the memory of a certain Per Knudsen. The wooden Madonna, bearing the infant Jesus, dates from the church's establishment. The other old Danish furnishings, including the altar, pulpit and epitaphs, were destroyed during an attack.
==Frescos== The church walls and vaults contain [[Church frescos in Sweden|late Gothic frescos]] painted by different 15th century masters. On the chancel wall, there is a painting of the martyrdom of [[Saint Erasmus]] with two executioners opening his stomach while God leads his soul into heaven. In the nave, the east vault displays three male heads while an arch to the south aisle has vestiges of Christ as a man of sorrow. In the sacristy, there are well preserved frescos from the early 16th century depicting the emblems of the [[four Evangelists|Evangelists]].<ref>[http://www.kyrkokartan.se/056126/B%C3%A5stads_kyrka "Båstads kyrka"], Kyrkokartan.se. {{sv icon}} Retrieved 9 September 2013.</ref>
